# Idea Roast: PRD Generator for Vibe Coders

**Date:** 2026-04-29
**Roasted by:** Paul Graham (simulated)

---

## The Idea

A web app that takes a founder's raw idea and generates a comprehensive, technically-complete PRD — including milestones, sequence diagrams, database schema, UI descriptions, test criteria, and risk mitigation — specifically designed to guide non-technical solopreneurs through the entire vibe-coding build process from start to finish.

**Target user:** Project managers and non-technical solopreneurs who want to build software using AI coding tools (Claude Code, Cursor, etc.) but lack the technical background to write a PRD detailed enough to survive the full build process.

---

## Round-by-Round Defense

### Round 1: Problem & Pain Point
The user identified a specific failure mode: non-technical PMs and solopreneurs start vibe-coding with incomplete PRDs, and the build breaks mid-process due to missing technical specifications (sequence diagrams, schema, security rules, edge cases). The customer is someone who understands *what* they want to build but cannot translate that into the technical detail an AI coding tool needs to execute consistently. Pain confirmed through direct conversation with a PM who experienced this exact failure.

### Round 2: Market Size & Validation
Market signal is thin but directionally valid. The vibe-coding wave has created a new class of builder — non-technical founders who can ship with AI but have no product discipline. PMs specifically are a strong beachhead: they already understand the value of a PRD and don't need to be educated on why it matters. They just need the technical layer they're missing. Community validation seen via LinkedIn and conferences where PMs are actively seeking answers about how to start building.

### Round 3: Competitors & Differentiation
Existing PRD tools (ChatGPT, Notion AI, generic AI assistants) stop at product descriptions and market analysis. They assume a technical developer will interpret and execute the PRD. This product goes further: it generates a complete build guide that covers milestones, test criteria, UI wireframe descriptions, sequence diagrams, risk mitigation, and review checklists — everything a solo non-technical builder needs to not just start but survive the entire build journey. The community layer (forum, peer discussion, mentoring) adds a dimension AI tools cannot replicate.

### Round 4: Business Model & Monetization
- **Price:** $50/month subscription
- **Go-to-market:** Building in public — founder uses their own tool to ship real products monthly, documents the journey on YouTube, attracts the exact audience (vibe-coding solopreneurs) who are already consuming this content
- **Differentiation from free AI tools:** Structured workflow specific to PRD generation + community of peers on the same journey — neither of which ChatGPT or Claude provides out of the box

