## Paul Graham's Verdict

**PIVOT TO BUILD**

**What you got right:**
- The pain is real and specific — non-technical PMs and solopreneurs break mid-build because their PRD isn't technical enough to survive contact with an AI coding tool
- The differentiation is genuine — not just PRD generation but a complete build guide covering milestones, test criteria, risk mitigation, and UI descriptions
- Building in public using your own product is the right go-to-market — it's proof, it's content, and it compounds

**What could still kill you:**
- You have no paying users yet and the market signal is thin — one conversation is not validation
- The community play is expensive to bootstrap — a ghost town forum kills trust faster than no forum at all
- Scope creep will destroy you — "beyond PRD" needs to be ruthlessly defined before you build, not after

**The one thing you must do next:**
Find 5 PMs or solopreneurs who have tried vibe-coding and failed mid-build. Show them a sample PRD your tool would generate. Ask if they'd pay $50/month for it. Don't build anything until you have 3 out of 5 saying yes.

**PG's parting shot:**
"You don't have a startup yet — you have a hypothesis. The fastest way to prove it is to make something so specific and so useful for one person that they'd be embarrassed to admit they can't live without it."